author: fitz
msg: More API/doxygen/documentation cleanup.
* subversion/include/svn_repos.h (svn_repos_fs_lock,
svn_repos_fs_unlock, svn_repos_fs_get_locks): Place these in a
doxygen defgroup which is new in 1.2 [instead of declaring it for
each function]).
(svn_repos_pre_lock_hook, svn_repos_post_lock_hook,
svn_repos_pre_unlock_hook, svn_repos_post_unlock_hook): Place in a
defgroup and mark it new in 1.2.

author: cmpilato
msg: Optimizations and bug fixes to r13767.
* subversion/libsvn_ra_dav/commit.c
(get_child_tokens): Just return the hash, not an error.
(commit_delete_entry): If a second DELETE attempt would be
effectively the same as the first, don't repeat it.  Also, in
preparation for directory locking, go ahead and add the delete
target's lock token to the list sent to the server (in addition to
the children already being sent).  Finally, don't leak the error
we get from the first DELETE attempt.
